@NODE "Problems"
   
   Problems:
   
      - Cybergraphics screens with a depth larger than 8-bit cause some
        windows to display very slowly.
        Solution: use 8-bit screens, only 32 colors are used at the
                  moment.
                  
      - Audio Evolution and an external MIDI sequencer are playing out of sync.
        Solution: use the Time Correction Factor in the @{"MIDI Settings" LINK "MIDI Settings Window"} window.
         
        
      - Delfina Lite has an incorrect sync with the 'any freq' modes
        
        Solution: Use another mode for now, the bug is again in the
                  AHI-driver. It's being fixed by Petsoff.
      
      - When you're hearing noise or clicks in the sound while playing
        back just one sample, try reducing the buffersize to around 8K.
        This for example helps when using the A4091 SCSI controller.


        
@ENDNODE

